Travis Scott and Kylie Jenner attend the premiere of Netflix's "Travis Scott: Look Mom I Can Fly" at Barker Hangar on August 27, 2019 in Santa Monica, California. JOHANNESBURG - Kylie Jenner and rapper Travis Scott have reportedly gone their separate ways. According to E! News, the couple is taking a break from their two-and-a-half year relationship following a series of fights. "Kylie and Travis aren't officially calling it quits on their relationship, but are taking space apart." "It's not a firm split. They've been fighting again, but have still seen each other within this last month", a source confirmed with E! News. Keeping up with Kylie: Jenner is world's youngest billionaire The source adds that the couple decided to stay in separate places in order to allow the situation to cool down. "Travis has been staying at his house in Beverly Hills and Kylie has been allowing him to see Stormi," the source said. "She would never take that away from him." The last time the couple was spotted together was during the premiere of the rapper's documentary, Look Mom, I Can Fly, in Santa Monica on 27 August.